<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-A1FEBAFA-7EB7-416C-BDD4-8DA7BC770809" version="3" lang="en-US"?><concept xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-A1FEBAFA-7EB7-416C-BDD4-8DA7BC770809" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic concept)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c concept oceConcept-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic concept/concept "><title class="- topic/title ">22 The start-up sequence of the printer</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-34C6A3E5-E809-4139-80CC-275A8CCF9EDC"><p class="- topic/p "> This document gives an overview of the activities during the start-up sequence of the printer. 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Functional description</category></metadata></prolog><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody "><section id="GUID-EF6DDE4F-EB35-408E-97EF-B7EEFFD183A1" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">The start-up sequence</title><table id="GUID-5B2FAFDA-6322-4717-9E30-6E1FF41D7B4C" pgwide="1" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="4" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="1.00*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="2.00*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="3.19*" align="left" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col4" colnum="4" colwidth="2.82*" align="left" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Time (in Minutes:Seconds) 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Description 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Additional information 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">00:00 
</p><note id="GUID-DC8587ED-BC60-46A7-A0BE-FC7986EA0A4E" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p "> The timing can slightly differ in different software releases 
</p></note></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Power switch (<comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Main Switch</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 22S1 </compcodenr></comp>) on. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">With the <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Main Switch</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 22S1 </compcodenr></comp> the system is switched on. The mains switch is only used in case there was a need to power down the system. Normally the system is switched from stand-by mode to operating mode using the green <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">On/off button</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 24S8 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">FRA_SOFT_ON_SW</compsignal></comp>.
</p><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Immediately after the mains switch is pushed, the <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname "> Windows controller PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 11PBA01 </compcodenr></comp>starts booting up. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> At the same time the 5V standby voltage of the Windows <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">ATX Supply</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 11G01 </compcodenr></comp> is used to activate relay K6 on <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">AC Switch</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 22PBA01 </compcodenr></comp>, which turns on the mains power for the <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Embedded controller PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 21PBA03 </compcodenr></comp> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> The green LED of the <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">On/off button</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 24S8 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">FRA_SOFT_ON_SW</compsignal></comp> blinks short (&lt;0.5 sec). 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">00:06 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> The Windows controller beeps 5 times and the backlight of the operator panel is activated (blue glow, panel is dark), indicating that there is power on L1. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">00:20 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> The operator panel shows a windows wheel. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">00:45 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Windows wheel disappears. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">01:30 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> The operator panel shows a 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Mountain image</b>. In this stage, the Windows controller software starts up. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">02:55 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The operator panel shows 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Go to Zero SDS</b> icon. Pushing the Zero SDS icon will indicate to the Windows controller that the system has to start up in Zero SDS. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">7 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">03:50 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> The green LED of the <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">On/off button</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 24S8 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">FRA_SOFT_ON_SW</compsignal></comp> lights up. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">8 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">03:55 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The operator panel shows the operating screen and initializing. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The Windows controller is initialized and will start the communication with the Embedded controller. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">AC Switch</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 22PBA01 </compcodenr></comp> relay K5 (clicking sound) switches on <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">24 VDC Supply</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 22G02 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">P_24V_1</compsignal></comp> (LED switch on) on, which powers; 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">* <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Distribution PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 22PBA02 </compcodenr></comp> is switched on (several LEDs on). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">* <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Ink supply PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 02PBA01 </compcodenr></comp> is switched on (several LEDs on). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">* <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">IOBOARD_BE PBA </compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 21PBA01 </compcodenr></comp> is switched on (several LEDs on). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">* <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">µMORPF PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 21PBA02</compcodenr></comp> is switched on (several LEDs on). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">* <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Carriage PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 05PBA07 </compcodenr></comp> is switched on (several LEDs on). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Next, the functions listed above will receive 24V and start to communicate with the <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Embedded controller PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 21PBA03 </compcodenr></comp>.
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">9 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">05:05 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">AC Switch</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 22PBA01 </compcodenr></comp> relay K3 (clicking sound) switches 36V 22G03 Power supply (LED switch on) on. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">AC Switch</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 22PBA01 </compcodenr></comp> relay K4 switches 49.5V (clicking sound) PHD 22G05 (led switch on) on. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> PHD function receives 49.5V and 36V. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The PWR_Drivers PBA 21PBA02 receives 36V. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">10 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">05:10 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">AC Switch</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 22PBA01 </compcodenr></comp> relay K1 switches 48V CUR function (LED switch on) on. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Curing function (UV Led Controller) receives 48V. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">11 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">05:30 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> The operator panel shows the operating screen. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">11* minutes remaining. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">AC Switch</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 22PBA01 </compcodenr></comp>relay K2 switches on the chiller. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The chiller shows the current temperature and the Normal LED (GREEN) is on. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The curing carriage moves the printhead carriage to the home position. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The ink refill LED's switch is on if a new bottle can be placed. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The media drawer LED switches on. The System starts all functions to go to Ready mode. (* = The displayed time will differ depending on the time the system was off). 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">12 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">06:40 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Curing carriage moves several times over the platen (print surface) (1 minute). 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">13 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">14:30 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The operator panel shows the operating screen. 1 minute remaining. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The printhead carriage moves several times over the platen (print surface)(30 seconds). 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">14 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">15.00 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The operator panel shows the operating screen. Ready: the printer is ready to print. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></conbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-B4557947-F0AA-4402-B5B4-34B41260F60F.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Functional description</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
</concept>